element.name: Project Planning Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Project Planning process is to produce and coordinate effective and workable plans.
Activities • Define the project • Plan project and technical management • Activate the project

element.name: Project Assessment and Control Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Project Assessment and Control process is to assess if the plans are aligned and feasible; determine the status of the project, technical and process performance; and direct execution to help ensure that the performance is according to plans and schedules, within projected budgets, to satisfy technical objectives.
Actvities:
Plan for project assessment and control Assess the project Control the project

element.name: Decision Management Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As defined by ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288
The purpose of the Decision Management process is to provide a structured, analytical framework for objectively identifying, characterizing and evaluating a set of alternatives for a decision at any point in the life cycle and select the most beneficial course of action.
Activities
Prepare for decisions Analyze the decison information Make and manage decisions
Taken from INCOSE Systems Engineering Handbook, John Wiley & Sons, Incorporated, 2023. ProQuest Ebook Central

element.name: Risk Management Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288, [6.3.4.1] The purpose of the Risk Management process is to identify, analyze, treat and monitor the risks continually.
Activties
Plan risk management Maintain the risk profile Analyze risks Treat risks that exceed their riks threshold Monitore risks
INCOSE Systems Engineering Handbook, John Wiley & Sons, Incorporated, 2023. ProQuest Ebook Central

element.name: Information Management Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Information Management process is to generate, obtain, confirm, transform, retain, retrieve, disseminate, and dispose of information to designated stakeholders.
Activities • Prepare for information management • Perform information management
INCOSE Systems Engineering Handbook, John Wiley & Sons, Incorporated, 2023. ProQuest Ebook Central

element.name: Measurement process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288 (and ISO/IEC/IEEE 15939),
The purpose of the Measurement process is to collect, analyze, and report objective data and information to support effective management and address information needs about the products, services, and processes.
Activities • Prepare for measurement • Perform measurement
INCOSE Systems Engineering Handbook, John Wiley & Sons, Incorporated, 2023. ProQuest Ebook Central

element.name: Quality Assurance process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Quality Assurance process is to help ensure the effective application of the organization’s Quality Management process to the project.
Typical Inputs • Quality management strategy/approach • Quality management criteria and methods • Quality management report • Quality management corrective action Activities • Prepare for quality assurance • Perform product or service evaluations • Perform process evaluations • Manage quality assurance records and reports • Treat incidents and problems
INCOSE Systems Engineering Handbook, John Wiley & Sons, Incorporated, 2023. ProQuest Ebook Central

element.name: System Analysis Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Transition process is to establish a capability for a system to provide services specified by stakeholder requirements in the operational environment.
Actvities Prepare for system analysis • Perform system analysis • Manage system analysis

element.name: Business or Mission Analysis Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288:
The purpose of the Business or Mission Analysis process is to define the overall strategic problem or opportunity, characterize the solution space, and determine potential solution class(es) that can address a problem or take advantage of an opportunity.
Actvities:
Prepare for business or mission analysis. Define the problem or opportunity space. Characterize the solution space. Evaluate alternative solution classes that span the potential solution space. Manage the Business or Mission Analysis.

element.name: Stakeholder Needs and Requirements Definition
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Stakeholder Needs and Requirements Definition process is to define the stakeholder needs and requirements for a system that can provide the capabilities needed by users and other stakeholders in a defined environment.

element.name: System Requierments Definition Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the System Requirements Definition process is to transform the stakeholder, user-oriented view of desired capabilities into a technical view of a solution that meets the operational needs of the user. Activities:
Prepare for system requirements definition Define system requirements. Define system requirements. Manage system requirements

element.name: System Architecture Definition Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the System Architecture Definition process is to generate system architecture alternatives, select one or more alternative(s) that address stakeholder concerns and system requirements, and express this in consistent views and models.
Activities
• Prepare for system architecture definition • Conceptualize the system architecture • Evaluate the system architecture • Elaborate the system architecture • Manage results of system architecture definition

element.name: Design Definition Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Design Definition process is to provide sufficient detailed data and information about the system and its elements to realize the solution in accordance with the system requirements and architecture.
Activities
Prepare for design definition • Create the system design • Evaluate the system design • Manage results of design definition

element.name: Implementation Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Implementation process is to realize a specified system element.
Actvities
Prepare for implementation • Perform implementation • Manage results of implementation

element.name: Validation Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Design Definition process is to provide sufficient detailed data and information about the system and its elements to realize the solution in accordance with the system requirements and architecture.
Actvities:
Prepare for validation Perform validation Manage results of validation

element.name: Verification Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Design Definition process is to provide sufficient detailed data and information about the system and its elements to realize the solution in accordance with the system requirements and architecture.

element.name: Integration Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Design Definition process is to provide sufficient detailed data and information about the system and its elements to realize the solution in accordance with the system requirements and architecture.

element.name: Disposal Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Disposal process is to end the existence of a system element or system for a specified intended use, appropriately handle replaced or retired elements, appropriately handle any waste products, and to properly attend to identified critical disposal needs.
Acvtities Prepare for disposal Perfrom disposal Finalize the disposal

element.name: Maintenance Process
element.documentation:
As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
[6.4.13] The purpose of the Maintenance process is to sustain the capability of the system to provide a service.
Activities
Prepare for maintenance and logistics Perform maintenance Perform logistics support Manage results of maintenance and logistics

element.name: Operation Process
element.documentation:
As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Operation process is to use the system to deliver its services.
Activities: Prepare for operation Perform operation Manage results of operation support stakeholders

element.name: Transition Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Transition process is to establish a capability for a system to provide services specified by stakeholder requirements in the operational environment.

element.name: Acquistion Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Acquisition process is to obtain a product or service in accordance with the acquirer’s requirements.
Activities Prepare for the acquisition. Advertise the acquisition and select the supplier. Establish and maintain an agreement. Monitor the agreement. Accept the product or service.

element.name: Supply Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Supply process is to provide an acquirer with a product or service that meets agreed requirements.
Activities:
Prepare for the supply. Respond to a request for supply of products or services. Establish and maintain an agreement. Execute the agreement. Deliver and support the product or service.

element.name: Life Cycle Model Management Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Life Cycle Model Management process is to define, maintain, and help ensure availability of policies, life cycle processes, life cycle models, and procedures for use by the organization with respect to the scope of ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288.
Activities:
Establish the life cycle processes Assess the life cycle processes Imrove the process

element.name: Infrastructure Management Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Infrastructure Management process is to provide the infrastructure and services to projects to support organization and project objectives throughout the life cycle.

element.name: Portfolio Management Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Portfolio Management process is to initiate and sustain necessary, sufficient, and suitable projects to meet the strategic objectives of the organization.
Activities
Define and authorize projects Evaluate the portfolio of projects Terminate projects

element.name: Human Resource Management Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Human Resource Management process is to provide the organization with necessary human resources and to maintain their competencies, consistent with strategic needs.
Actvities:
Identify skills Develop skills Acquie and provide skills

element.name: Quality Management Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Quality Management process is to assure that products, services, and implementations of the Quality Management process meet organizational and project quality objectives and achieve customer satisfaction.
Activities
Plan quality management Assess quality management Perform quality management corrective and preventive action

element.name: Knowledge Management Process
element.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Knowledge Management process is to create the capability and assets that enable the organization to exploit opportunities to re-apply existing knowledge.
Actvities:
Plan knowledge management Share knowledge and skills throuout organziation Share knowledge assets throuout the organization Managne knowledge, skills and knowledge assets

element.name: Operation procedure
element.documentation: Presents an ordered series of steps to perform operation.

element.name: Organization infrastructure
element.documentation: Resources, facilities, personnel, and/or services that support the organization.

element.name: Accepted system or system element
element.documentation: System or system element (product or service) accepted by an acquirer from a supplier consistent with the delivery conditions of the supply agreement.

element.name: Acquired system or system element
element.documentation: System or system element (product or service) delivered to the acquirer from a supplier consistent with the delivery conditions of the acquisition agreement.

element.name: Acquisition agreement
element.documentation: Mutual acknowledgment of terms and conditions under which a working relationship is conducted between an acquirer and a supplier. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288, 2023).

element.name: Acquisition need
element.documentation: Identified need that cannot be met within the organization encountering the need or a need that can be met in a more economical way by a supplier.

element.name: Acquisition payment
element.documentation: Payments or other compensations for an acquired system.

element.name: Acquisition records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to acquisition.

element.name: Acquisition report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the acquisition activities.

element.name: Acquisition strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform acquisition.

element.name: Agreements
element.documentation: Agreements from all applicable life cycle processes, including: acquisition agreement and supply agreement.

element.name: Alternative solution classes
element.documentation: Identifies and describes the classes of solutions that may address the problem or opportunity.

element.name: Analysis Situation
element.documentation: Analyses that arise from any stakeholder. Can originate from any life cycle process.

element.name: Applicable laws and regulations
element.documentation: International, national, or local laws or regulations.

element.name: Breakdown structures
element.documentation: Hierarchical representations of project aspects into smaller components providing the necessary frameworks to accomplish the project objectives and create the required deliverables.

element.name: Business or mission analysis records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to business or mission analysis.

element.name: Business or mission analysis report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the business or mission analysis activities.

element.name: Business or mission analysis strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform business or mission analysis.

element.name: Business plan
element.documentation: The overall organization business plan, including the business objectives.

element.name: Candidate Items for configuration management
element.documentation: Items for configuration control. Can originate from any life cycle process.

element.name: Candidate items for information management
element.documentation: Items for information control. Can originate from any life cycle process.

element.name: Candidate risks and opportunities
element.documentation: Risks and opportunities that arise from any stakeholder. Can originate from any life cycle process.

element.name: Change request
element.documentation: Identified anomaly, required, or recommended enhancement to a project, from the time an idea is recorded until the disposition by a designated change authority. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 24765, 2017).

element.name: Concept of operations (ConOps)
element.documentation: At the organization level, addresses the leadership’s intended way of operating the organization (ISO/IEC/IEEE 29148, 2018).

element.name: Configuration baseline
element.documentation: Configuration information formally designated at a specific time during the life of a product, product component, service, or service component. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 24765, 2017).

element.name: Configuration management records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to configuration management.

element.name: Configuration management report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the configuration management activities.

element.name: Configuration management system
element.documentation: System used to support and enable configuration management.

element.name: Configuration managemnt strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform configuration management.

element.name: Configuration verification and audit report
element.documentation: Provides results of configuration management verifications and audits to ensure adequate traceability, control, and visibility. It includes evaluation criteria.

element.name: Constraints on solution
element.documentation: Externally imposed limitation on the system, its design, or implementation or on the process used to develop or modify a system. (ISO/IEC/IEEE 29148, 2018).

element.name: Critical performance measurement data
element.documentation: Data provided for the identified system-of-interest measurement needs.

element.name: Critical performance measurement needs
element.documentation: Identified information needs of the decision makers with respect to system-of-interest expectations.

element.name: Customer satisfaction inputs
element.documentation: Responses to customer satisfaction surveys or other instruments.

element.name: Decision management strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform decision management.

element.name: Decision register
element.documentation: A repository that supports the availability for use and communication of all relevant decision information in a timely, complete, valid, and, if required, confidential manner.

element.name: Decision situations
element.documentation: Decisions that arise from any stakeholder. Can originate from any life cycle process.

element.name: Design definition records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to design definition.

element.name: Design definition report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the design definition activities.

element.name: Design definition strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform design definition.

element.name: Disposal procedure
element.documentation: Presents an ordered series of steps to perform disposal.

element.name: Disposal records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to disposal.

element.name: Disposal report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the disposal activities.

element.name: Disposal strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform disposal.

element.name: Disposed system
element.documentation: System (product or service) that has been deactivated, disassembled, and removed from operations and been properly disposed.

element.name: Enabling systems
element.documentation: External systems that facilitate the life cycle activities of the SoI but are not a direct element of the operational environment.

element.name: Human resource management records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to human resource management.

element.name: Human resource management report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the human resource management activities.

element.name: Human resource management strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform human resource management.

element.name: Implementation records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to implementation.

element.name: Implementation report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the implementation activities.

element.name: Implementation strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform implementation.

element.name: Information management records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to information management.

element.name: Information management report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the information management activities.

element.name: Information management strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform information management.

element.name: Information register
element.documentation: A repository that supports the availability for use and communication of all relevant project information artifacts in a timely, complete, valid, and, if required, restricted manner.

element.name: Infrastructure management records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to infrastructure management.

element.name: Infrastructure management report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the infrastructure management activities.

element.name: Infrastructure management strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform infrastructure management.

element.name: Installation procedure
element.documentation: Presents an ordered series of steps to perform transition.

element.name: Installed system
element.documentation: System (product or service) that has been installed in its operational environment.

element.name: Integrated system or system element
element.documentation: System or system element (product or service) that has been aggregated from system elements.

element.name: Integration procedure
element.documentation: Presents an ordered series of steps to perform integration.

element.name: Integration records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to integration.

element.name: Integration report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the integration activities.

element.name: Integration strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform integration.

element.name: Knowledge management records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to knowledge management.

element.name: Knowledge management report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the knowledge management activities.

element.name: Knowledge management strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform knowledge management.

element.name: Knowledge management system
element.documentation: System used to support and enable knowledge management.

element.name: Life cycle concepts
element.documentation: Articulation and refinement of the various life cycle concepts consistent with the stakeholder needs. Typical concepts include: acquisition concept; deployment concept; operational concept (OpsCon); support concept; retirement conce

element.name: Life cycle model management records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to life cycle model management.

element.name: Life cycle model management report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the life cycle model management activities.

element.name: Life cycle model management strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform life cycle model management.

element.name: Life cycle models
element.documentation: Framework of processes and activities concerned with the life cycle that can be organized into stages, acting as a common reference for communication and understanding. (ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288, 2023)

element.name: Maintained and sustained system
element.documentation: System (product or service) that has been maintained for use in its operational environment.

element.name: Maintenance and logistics procedure
element.documentation: Presents an ordered series of steps to perform maintenance.

element.name: Maintenance and logistics records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to maintenance.

element.name: Maintenance and logistics report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the maintenance activities.

element.name: Maintenance and logistics strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform maintenance.

element.name: Measurement data
element.documentation: Measurement data from all applicable life cycle processes, including: critical performance measurement data, organizational measurement data, and project measurement data.

element.name: Measurement needs
element.documentation: Measurement needs from all applicable life cycle processes, including: critical performance measurement needs, organizational measurement needs, and project measurement needs.

element.name: Measurement records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to measurement.

element.name: Measurement register
element.documentation: A repository that supports the availability for use and communication of all relevant measures in a timely, complete, valid, and, if required, confidential manner.

element.name: Measurement report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the measurement activities.

element.name: Measurement strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform measurement.

element.name: Operational system
element.documentation: System (product or service) being used in its operational environment.

element.name: Operation records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to operation.

element.name: Operation report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the operation activities.

element.name: Operation strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform operation.

element.name: Organization infrastructure needs
element.documentation: Identified organizational infrastructure needs.

element.name: Organization strategic plan
element.documentation: The overall organization strategy, including the business mission or vision and strategic goals and objectives.

element.name: Organization tailoring strategy/approach
element.documentation: Organization’s specific strategy and approach to tailoring required to incorporate new or updated external standards.

element.name: Other verified artifacts
element.documentation: Artifacts that are verified

element.name: Problem or opportunity statement
element.documentation: Description of the problem or opportunity. Should be derived from the organization strategy and provide enough detail to understand the gap or new capability that is being considered

element.name: Project authorization
element.documentation: Authorization from the organization to proceed per the agreed-to project plan.

element.name: Project authorization request
element.documentation: Request from the project to the organization to authorize the project.

element.name: Project budget
element.documentation: Estimate of the costs associated with a particular project. Includes labor, infrastructure, acquisition, and enabling system costs along with reserves for risk management.

element.name: Project constraints
element.documentation: Externally imposed limitation on the project developing or modifying a system. (ISO/IEC/IEEE 29148, 2018)

element.name: Project human resource needs
element.documentation: Identified human resource needs of the project.

element.name: Project infrastructure needs
element.documentation: Identified infrastructure needs of the project.

element.name: Project lessons learned
element.documentation: Project-related lessons learned. Results from an evaluation or observation of an implemented corrective action that contributed to improved performance or increased capability. A lesson learned also results from an evaluation or observation of a positive finding that did not necessarily require corrective action other than sustainment.

element.name: Project objectives
element.documentation: The objectives or goals for the project.

element.name: Project planning records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to project planning.

element.name: Project portfolio
element.documentation: Collection of projects that addresses the strategic objectives of the organization. (ISO/IEC/IEEE 12207, 2017)

element.name: Project schedule
element.documentation: A linked list of a project’s milestones, activities, and deliverables with intended start and finish dates May include a top-level milestone schedule and multiple levels (also called tiers) of schedules of increasing detail and task descriptions with completion criteria and work authorizations.

element.name: Project tailoring strategy/approach
element.documentation: Project’s specific strategy and approach to tailoring required to incorporate new or updated life cycle models.

element.name: Qualified personnel
element.documentation: Individuals equipped to perform duties on behalf of the organization, including officers, employees, and contractors. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 24765, 2017)

element.name: Quality management corrective action
element.documentation: Action to eliminate the cause or reduce the likelihood of recurrence of a detected organizational nonconformity or other undesirable situation. (Adapted from ISO/IEC 19770–1, 2017)

element.name: Quality management evaluation report
element.documentation: Provides results of quality management evaluations. It includes evaluation criteria. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15289, 2019)

element.name: Requirements imposed on enabling systems
element.documentation: Identified requirements for enabling systems of the system-of-interest.

element.name: Reused system or system element
element.documentation: System or system element (product or service) reused by an organization consistent with its system element requirements.

element.name: Source documents
element.documentation: External documents relevant to the particular stage of the system of interest.

element.name: Stakeholder identification
element.documentation: List of individuals or organizations having a right, share, claim, or interest in a system or in its possession of characteristics that meet their needs and expectations. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288, 2023)

element.name: Stakeholder needs and requirements
element.documentation: Structured collection of the requirements [characteristics, context, concepts, constraints and priorities] of the stakeholder and the relationship to the external environment. (ISO/IEC/IEEE 29148, 2018)

element.name: Stakeholder needs and requirements definition records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to stakeholder needs and requirements definition.

element.name: Stakeholder needs and requirements definition report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the stakeholder needs and requirements definition activities.

element.name: Stakeholder needs and requirements definition strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform stakeholder needs and requirements definition.

element.name: Supply response
element.documentation: Prepared by a potential supplier to support the offer of a contract bid, including cost, schedule, risk statements, methodology to satisfy the request for supply, experiences and capabilities, any recommendations to tailor the request for supply or contract, and the signature of the supplier’s approving authority. Informally, may be prepared within an organization. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15289, 2019)

element.name: System analysis records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to system analysis.

element.name: System analysis report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the system analysis activities.

element.name: System analysis request
element.documentation: A request to conduct a system analysis.

element.name: System analysis strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform system analysis.

element.name: System architecture assessment report
element.documentation: Provides results of system architecture assessments. It includes evaluation criteria. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15289, 2019)

element.name: System architecture definition records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to system architecture definition.

element.name: System architecture definition report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the system architecture definition activities.

element.name: System architecture definition strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform system architecture definition.

element.name: System architecture description
element.documentation: The fundamental conception of a system-of-interest in terms of its purpose, system qualities (such as feasibility, performance, safety, and interoperability), constraints, and design decisions and rationale. Identification of the architecture’s stakeholders and the stakeholders’ architecture-related concerns. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15289, 2019)

element.name: System architecture rationale
element.documentation: Rationale for architecture selection, technological/technical system element selection, and allocation between system requirements and architectural entities.

element.name: System design assessment report
element.documentation: Provides results of system design assessments. It includes evaluation criteria. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15289, 2019)

element.name: System design characteristics
element.documentation: Design attributes or distinguishing features that pertain to a measurable description of a product or service. (ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288, 2023)

element.name: System design description
element.documentation: Describes the design of a system or element. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 24765, 2017)

element.name: System design rationale
element.documentation: Rationale for design selection, system element selection, and allocation between system requirements and system elements. Includes rationale of major selected implementation options and enablers.

element.name: System element
element.documentation: System element (product or service) implemented consistent with its system element requirements.

element.name: System element description
element.documentation: Applies the system architecture description to the low-level system configuration items and elements. It is at a level of detail to permit design, implementation, and test. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15289, 2019)

element.name: System interface definition
element.documentation: Description of the interfaces between systems and system elements. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 24765, 2017)

element.name: System requirements
element.documentation: Structured collection of the requirements [functions, performance, design constraints, and other attributes] for the system and its operational environments and external interfaces. (ISO/IEC/IEEE 29148, 2018)

element.name: System requirements definition records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to system requirements definition.

element.name: System requirements definition report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the system requirements definition activities.

element.name: System requirements definition strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform system requirements definition.

element.name: Systems engineering management plan (SEMP)
element.documentation: Presents how the project processes and activities are executed to assure the project’s successful completion, and the quality of the deliverable product or service. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15289, 2019)

element.name: System viewpoints, views, and models
element.documentation: Definitions of viewpoints to document the procedures for creating, interpreting, analyzing, and evaluating architectural data. One or more views of the system. Each architectural view is a representation of the complete system from the perspective of one or more system concerns, for its stakeholders. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15289, 2019)

element.name: Traceability mapping
element.documentation: Records the relationship between two or more artifacts of the development process (e.g., requirements, functions, system elements, verifications, and validations, tasks). (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 24765, 2017)

element.name: Training materials
element.documentation: Materials for the provision of formal and informal learning activities. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 24765, 2017)

element.name: Validated stakeholder needs and requirements
element.documentation: Set of stakeholder needs and requirements that have been validated.

element.name: Validated system architecture and design
element.documentation: System architecture and design that has been validated.

element.name: Validation criteria
element.documentation: The validation criteria (the measures to be assessed), who will perform validation activities, and the validation environments of the system-of-interest.

element.name: Variance/deviation/waiver request
element.documentation: Request, temporary or permanent, to accept a configuration item or other designated item which, during production or after having been submitted for inspection, is found to depart from specified requirements, but is nevertheless considered suitable for use as is or after rework by an approved method. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 24765, 2017)

element.name: Verification criteria
element.documentation: The verification criteria (the measures to be assessed), who will perform verification activities, and the verification environments of the system-of-interest.

element.name: Verification procedure
element.documentation: Presents an ordered series of steps to perform verification.

element.name: Verification records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to verification.

element.name: Verification report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the verification activities.

element.name: Verification strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform verification.

element.name: Verified system
element.documentation: System (product or service) that has been verified.

element.name: Verified system architecture and design
element.documentation: System architecture and design that has been verified.

element.name: Verified system requirements
element.documentation: Set of system requirements that have been verified.

element.name: Organization lessons learned
element.documentation: Organizational-related lessons learned. Results from an evaluation or observation of an implemented corrective action that contributed to improved performance or increased capability. A lesson learned also results from an evaluation or observation of a positive finding that did not necessarily require corrective action other than sustainment.

element.name: Organization policies
element.documentation: High-level direction at the organizational level consistent with the organization’s strategies. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15289, 2019)

element.name: Organization portfolio direction and constraints
element.documentation: Organization direction and constraints related to the project portfolio.

element.name: Organization procedures
element.documentation: Presents an ordered series of steps to perform a process, activity, or task for an organization. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15289, 2019)

element.name: Organization processes
element.documentation: Set of interrelated or interacting activities that transform inputs into outputs for an organization. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288, 2023)

element.name: Organization reports
element.documentation: Reports from all applicable organization life cycle processes, including: life cycle model management report, infrastructure management report, portfolio management report, human resource management report, quality management report, and knowledge management report.

element.name: Organization strategies/approaches
element.documentation: Strategies/approaches for all applicable organization life processes, including: life cycle model management strategy/approach, infrastructure management strategy/approach, portfolio management strategy/approach, human resource management strategy/approach, quality management strategy/approach, and knowledge management strategy/approach.

element.name: Organizational measurement data
element.documentation: Data provided for the identified organizational measurement needs.

element.name: Organizational measurement needs
element.documentation: Identified information needs of the decision makers with respect to organizational expectations.

element.name: Other validated artifacts
element.documentation: Artifacts that are validated

element.name: Portfolio management records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to portfolio management.

element.name: Portfolio management report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the portfolio management activities.

element.name: Portfolio management strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform portfolio management.

element.name: Problem or opportunity statement
element.documentation: Description of the problem or opportunity. Should be derived from the organization strategy and provide enough detail to understand the gap or new capability that is being considered

element.name: Project assessment and control records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to project assessment and control.

element.name: Project assessment and control strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform project assessment and control.

element.name: Project control request
element.documentation: Project directives based on action required due to deviations from the project plan. If assessments are associated with a decision gate, a decision to proceed or not to proceed, is taken.

element.name: Project decision gate/review result
element.documentation: Decision gate and review artifacts that are expected through conduct of the decision gate or technical review and that can be considered elements of exit criteria. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 24748–8, 2019)

element.name: Project direction
element.documentation: Organizational direction to the project. Includes sustainment of projects meeting objectives and redirection or termination of projects not meeting objectives.

element.name: Project infrastructure
element.documentation: Resources, facilities, personnel, and/or services that support the project.

element.name: Project measurement data
element.documentation: Data provided for the identified project measurement needs.

element.name: Project measurement needs
element.documentation: Identified information needs of the decision makers with respect to project expectations.

element.name: Project procedures
element.documentation: Procedures from all applicable life cycle processes, including: integration procedure, verification procedure, installation procedure, validation procedure, operation procedure, maintenance and logistics procedure, and disposal procedure.

element.name: Project reports
element.documentation: Reports from all applicable project life cycle processes, including: acquisition report, supply report, decision management report, risk management report, configuration management report, configuration verification and audit report, information management report, measurement report, quality assurance report, quality assurance evaluation report, business or mission analysis report, stakeholder needs and requirements definition report, system requirements definition report, system architecture definition report, system architecture assessment report, design definition report, system design assessment report, system analysis report, implementation report, integration report, verification report, transition report, validation report, operation report, maintenance and logistics report, and disposal report.

element.name: Project status report/dashboard
element.documentation: Provides results of monitoring the execution of the defined plan or processes for internal or external distribution. It includes a summary of decisions, monitoring results, action items, process or performance data, and recorded process improvements. It assesses the degree of adherence to the plans. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15289, 2019)

element.name: Project strategies/approaches
element.documentation: Strategies/approaches for all applicable project life processes, including: acquisition strategy/approach, supply strategy & approach, project assessment and control strategy/approach, decision management strategy/approach, risk management strategy/approach, configuration management strategy/approach, information management strategy/approach, measurement strategy/approach, quality assurance strategy/approach, business or mission analysis strategy/approach, stakeholder needs and requirements definition strategy/approach, system requirements definition strategy/approach, system architecture definition strategy/approach, design definition strategy/approach, system analysis strategy/approach, implementation strategy/approach, integration strategy/approach, verification strategy/approach, transition strategy/approach, validation strategy/approach, operation strategy/approach, maintenance and logistics strategy/approach, and disposal strategy/approach.

element.name: Quality assurance corrective action
element.documentation: Action to eliminate the cause or reduce the likelihood of recurrence of a detected project nonconformity or other undesirable situation. (Adapted from ISO/IEC 19770–1, 2017)

element.name: Quality assurance evaluation report
element.documentation: Provides results of quality assurance evaluations. It includes evaluation criteria. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15289, 2019)

element.name: Quality assurance records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to quality assurance.

element.name: Quality assurance report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the quality assurance activities.

element.name: Quality assurance strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform quality assurance.

element.name: Quality assurance system
element.documentation: System used to support and enable quality assurance.

element.name: Quality management criteria and methods
element.documentation: Rules on which a judgment or decision can be based, or by which an organization can be evaluated. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15289, 2019)

element.name: Quality management records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to quality management.

element.name: Quality management report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the quality management activities.

element.name: Quality management strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform quality management

element.name: Quality management system
element.documentation: System used to support and enable quality management.

element.name: Records/artifacts
element.documentation: Records from all applicable life cycle processes, including: acquisition records/artifacts, supply records/artifacts, life cycle model management records/artifacts, infrastructure management records/artifacts, portfolio management records/artifacts, human resource management records/artifacts, quality management records/artifacts, knowledge management records/artifacts, project planning records/artifacts, project assessment and control records/artifacts, decision management records/artifacts, risk management records/artifacts, configuration management records/artifacts, information management records/artifacts, measurement records/artifacts, quality assurance records/artifacts, business or mission analysis records/artifacts, stakeholder needs and requirements definition records/artifacts, system requirements definition records/artifacts, system architecture definition records/artifacts, design definition records/artifacts, system analysis records/artifacts, implementation records/artifacts, integration records/artifacts, verification records/artifacts, transition records/artifacts, validation records/artifacts, operation records/artifacts, maintenance and logistics records/artifacts, disposal records/artifacts, tailoring records/artifacts.

element.name: Request for supply
element.documentation: Acquirer’s request for information and commitments needed from the supplier that are required to be included in the potential supplier’s proposal. It announces the acquirer’s intention to potential bidders to acquire a specified system or system element (product or service). (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15289, 2019)

element.name: Risk management records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to risk management.

element.name: Risk management report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the risk management activities.

element.name: Risk management strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform risk management.

element.name: Risk register
element.documentation: A repository that supports the availability for use and communication of all relevant risk information in a timely, complete, valid, and, if required, confidential manner.

element.name: Standards
element.documentation: This handbook and relevant industry, country, military, acquirer, and other specifications and standards. Includes new knowledge from industry sponsored knowledge networks.

element.name: Supplied system or system element
element.documentation: System or system element (product or service) delivered from a supplier to an acquirer consistent with the delivery conditions of the supply agreement.

element.name: Supply agreement
element.documentation: Mutual acknowledgment of terms and conditions under which a working relationship is conducted between a supplier and an acquirer. (Adapted from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288, 2023)

element.name: Supply payment
element.documentation: Payments or other compensations for the supplied system.

element.name: Supply records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to supply.

element.name: Supply report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the supply activities.

element.name: Supply strategy/ approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform supply.

element.name: Tailoring records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to tailoring.

element.name: Trained personnel
element.documentation: Trained individuals or organizations that perform the operation, maintenance, or other functions of or for a system.

element.name: Transition records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to transition.

element.name: Transition report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the transition activities.

element.name: Transition strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform transition.

element.name: Validated system
element.documentation: System (product or service) that has been validated.

element.name: Validation procedure
element.documentation: Presents an ordered series of steps to perform validation.

element.name: Validation records/artifacts
element.documentation: Permanent, readable form of data, information, or knowledge related to validation.

element.name: Validation report
element.documentation: An account prepared for interested parties in order to communicate the status, results, and outcomes of the validation activities.

element.name: Validation strategy/approach
element.documentation: Approaches, schedules, resources, and specific considerations required to perform validation.

view.name: Life Cycle Model Management Process
view.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Life Cycle Model Management process is to define, maintain, and help ensure availability of policies, life cycle processes, life cycle models, and procedures for use by the organization with respect to the scope of ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288.
Activities:
Estabish the life cycle processes Assess the life cycle processes Improve the process

view.name: Portfolio Management Process
view.documentation:
Purpose As stated in ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288,
The purpose of the Portfolio Management process is to initiate and sustain necessary, sufficient, and suitable projects to meet the strategic objectives of the organization.
Activities
Define and authorize projects Evaluate the portfolio of prjects Tmerinate projects
